Citation.sAbstract: Activity coefficients at infinite dilution,    13, for 32 organic compounds: alkanes, alk-1-enes, alk-1-ynes,  cycloalkanes, aromatic hydrocarbons, alcohols, thiophene, tetrahydrofuran, tert-butyl methyl ether and  water in the ionic liquid 1-butyl-1-methylpyrrolidinium trifluoromethanesulfonate [BMPYR][CF3SO3]  were determined by gas.liquid chromatography at the temperatures ranging from 298.15 to 368.15 K.  The partial molar excess enthalpies at infinite dilution  HE,   1 were calculated from the experimental     13 values obtained over the temperature range. The selectivities for the n-hexane/benzene,  cyclohexane/benzene, n-hexane/thiophene, cyclohexane/thiophene, benzene/thiophene and hexen-1-  ene/n-hexane separation problems were calculated from the    13 and compared to the literature values  for other ionic liquids, NMP and sulfolane.
